sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as Resume Visitor
    participant Browser as Web Browser
    participant Pages as GitHub Pages (Static Host)
    participant Landing as index.html (Generated in CI)
    participant PDF as resume.pdf (Generated in CI)

    Note over User,Pages: Static client only (no custom frontend framework in repository)

    User->>Browser: Navigate to /latest-resume/
    Browser->>Browser: Enter loading state (document request pending)
    Browser->>Pages: GET /latest-resume/
    alt index.html available
        Pages-->>Browser: 200 OK + Landing HTML
        Browser->>Landing: Parse and render page content
        Note over Browser,Landing: UI components are static HTML elements (title, description, CTA link)
        Note over Browser: No client-side state manager/store exists, state is browser-native (loading/render/error)
        Note over Browser,Pages: No API calls are made to an application backend.
        Note over Browser,Pages: No authentication flow is implemented for viewers.
    else index.html missing or inaccessible
        Pages-->>Browser: 404/5xx
        Browser->>User: Show browser error page
    end

    opt User clicks "Open resume.pdf"
        User->>Browser: Click CTA link
        Browser->>Browser: Navigate route to ./resume.pdf
        Browser->>Browser: Enter loading state (PDF request pending)
        Browser->>Pages: GET /latest-resume/resume.pdf
        alt PDF exists
            Pages-->>Browser: 200 OK + PDF bytes
            Browser->>User: Render/download PDF
        else PDF missing or unavailable
            Pages-->>Browser: 404/5xx
            Browser->>User: Show failed file load/download error
        end
    end

    loop Subsequent visits or refreshes
        User->>Browser: Refresh page or revisit URL
        Browser->>Pages: Re-request static assets (or use browser cache)
    end
